Top businesswoman Dr. Thandi Ndlovu has died in a car crash near Rustenburg in North West. Details around the crash are still sketchy but it is believed that she and other occupants, died in a head-on collision.  The African National Congress (ANC) says Ndlovu, who was a former president of the Black Business Council for the Built Environment, was a freedom fighter and feminist. The party says Ndlovu spent her free time caring for veteran stalwarts like Adelaide Tambo and Ruth Mompati. During the liberation struggle she was part of uMkhonto Wesizwe. The ANC has sent its heartfelt condolences to her family.  Others have also taken to social media to send tributes to the late businesswoman.   